
---


@startuml

package "Louvre Museum System" {
    [Location] as L
    [Exhibition] as E
    [ExhibitionItem] as EI
    [Piece] as P
    [Collector] as C
    [Employee] as Em
    [Coaching] as Co
}

L --|> E : contains
E "1" --o"0..*" EI : has
EI -- P : requires
EI -- C : sourced from
P -- C : belongs to
Em "1" --o"0..*" Co : has coach
Em -- EI : is coordinator of
Co -- Em : coach of
Co -- Em : coached by

note right of L
  - ID
  - Name
  - Description
  - Capacity
end note

note right of E
  - ID
  - Title
  - Start Date
  - End Date
  - Coordinator (Employee)
end note

note right of EI
  - ID
  - Title
  - Description
  - Required Quantity
  - Status
end note

note right of P
  - ID
  - Title
  - Artist
  - Description
  - Availability
end note

note right of C
  - ID
  - Name
  - Contact Info
  - Location
end note

note right of Em
  - ID
  - Name
  - Position
  - Email
  - Coach (Employee)
end note

note right of Co
  - Coach (Employee)
  - Coachee (Employee)
end note

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Relationships

- **Location** contains multiple **Exhibitions**.
- Each **Exhibition** has one or more **ExhibitionItems**.
- Each **ExhibitionItem** requires a **Piece** and may be sourced from a **Collector**.
- A **Collector** can supply multiple **Pieces**.
- An **Employee** can be the **Coordinator** of an **Exhibition**.
- An **Employee** can have a **Coach** (another **Employee**) via a **Coaching** relationship.
- The **Coaching** relationship links a **Coach** to a **Coachee**.

